<h5>Counter-rucking</h5>

<p>If you're unable to jackal the ball because a ruck has formed, your next option is to counter-ruck. This is where you simply push the opposition players off the ball. Stay on your feet and bind on to the players. You can take a run-up to hit them off the ball, but if you shoulder-charge without binding onto them or hit anyone in their head you'll be penalised or sent-off. You should only counter-ruck when you know you can do it successfully. So, if there are 2 or more players to push out of the way, then it's probably worthless to try.</p>

